#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn36.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.11:0.2"
msgid "2. Rahogatavagga "
msgstr "2. In Private "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 11. Rahogatasutta → rahogataka (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Rahogatasutta "
msgstr "11. In Private "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn36.11:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.11:1.2"
msgid "“idha mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi—"
msgstr "“Just now, sir, as I was in private retreat this thought came to mind. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:1.3"
msgid "tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr "The Buddha has spoken of three feelings. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:1.4"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr "Pleasant, painful, and neutral feeling. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:1.5"
msgid "imā tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr "These are the three feelings the Buddha has spoken of. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.11:1.6"
msgid "Vuttaṃ kho panetaṃ bhagavatā: "
msgstr "But the Buddha has also said: "

msgctxt "sn36.11:1.7"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci vedayitaṃ taṃ dukkhasmin’ti. "
msgstr "‘Suffering includes whatever is felt.’ "

msgctxt "sn36.11:1.8"
msgid "Kiṃ nu kho etaṃ bhagavatā sandhāya bhāsitaṃ: "
msgstr "What was the Buddha referring to when he said this?” "

msgctxt "sn36.11:1.9"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci vedayitaṃ taṃ dukkhasmin’”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.217, sc2
msgctxt "sn36.11:2.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhu. "
msgstr "“Good, good, mendicant! "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.2"
msgid "Tisso imā, bhikkhu, vedanā vuttā mayā. "
msgstr "I have spoken of these three feelings. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.3"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr "Pleasant, painful, and neutral feeling. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.4"
msgid "imā tisso vedanā vuttā mayā. "
msgstr "These are the three feelings I have spoken of. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.11:2.5"
msgid "Vuttaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhu, mayā: "
msgstr "But I have also said: "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.6"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci vedayitaṃ, taṃ dukkhasmin’ti. "
msgstr "‘Suffering includes whatever is felt.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.11:2.7"
msgid "Taṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhu, mayā saṅkhārānaṃyeva aniccataṃ sandhāya bhāsitaṃ: "
msgstr "When I said this I was referring to the impermanence of conditions, to the fact that conditions are "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.8"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci vedayitaṃ taṃ dukkhasmin’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.9"
msgid "Taṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhu, mayā saṅkhārānaṃyeva khayadhammataṃ … pe … "
msgstr "liable to end, "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.10"
msgid "vayadhammataṃ … pe … "
msgstr "vanish, "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.11"
msgid "virāgadhammataṃ … pe … "
msgstr "fade away, "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.12"
msgid "nirodhadhammataṃ … pe … "
msgstr "cease, "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.13"
msgid "vipariṇāmadhammataṃ sandhāya bhāsitaṃ: "
msgstr "and perish. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.14"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci vedayitaṃ taṃ dukkhasmin’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.11:2.15"
msgid "Atha kho pana, bhikkhu, mayā anupubbasaṅkhārānaṃ nirodho akkhāto. "
msgstr "But I have also explained the progressive cessation of conditions. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.16"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa vācā niruddhā hoti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the first absorption, speech has ceased. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.17"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa vitakkavicārā niruddhā honti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the second absorption, the placing of the mind and keeping it connected have ceased. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.18"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa pīti niruddhā hoti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the third absorption, rapture has ceased. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.19"
msgid "Catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa assāsapassāsā niruddhā honti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the fourth absorption, breathing has ceased. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.20"
msgid "Ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samāpannassa rūpasaññā niruddhā hoti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the dimension of infinite space, the perception of form has ceased. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.21"
msgid "Viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samāpannassa ākāsānañcāyatanasaññā niruddhā hoti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the dimension of infinite consciousness, the perception of the dimension of infinite space has ceased. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.22"
msgid "Ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samāpannassa viññāṇañcāyatanasaññā niruddhā hoti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the dimension of nothingness, the perception of the dimension of infinite consciousness has ceased. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.23"
msgid "Nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samāpannassa ākiñcaññāyatanasaññā niruddhā hoti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, the perception of the dimension of nothingness has ceased. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.24"
msgid "Saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpannassa saññā ca vedanā ca niruddhā honti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling, perception and feeling have ceased. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.25"
msgid "Khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno rāgo niruddho hoti, doso niruddho hoti, moho niruddho hoti. "
msgstr "For a mendicant who has ended the defilements, greed, hate, and delusion have ceased. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.11:2.26"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhu, mayā anupubbasaṅkhārānaṃ vūpasamo akkhāto. "
msgstr "And I have also explained the progressive stilling of conditions. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.27"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa vācā vūpasantā hoti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the first absorption, speech has stilled. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.28"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa vitakkavicārā vūpasantā honti … pe … "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the second absorption, the placing of the mind and keeping it connected have stilled. … "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.29"
msgid "saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpannassa saññā ca vedanā ca vūpasantā honti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling, perception and feeling have stilled. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.30"
msgid "Khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno rāgo vūpasanto hoti, doso vūpasanto hoti, moho vūpasanto hoti. "
msgstr "For a mendicant who has ended the defilements, greed, hate, and delusion have stilled. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.11:2.31"
msgid "Chayimā, bhikkhu, passaddhiyo. "
msgstr "There are these six levels of tranquility. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.32"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa vācā paṭippassaddhā hoti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the first absorption, speech has been tranquilized. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.33"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa vitakkavicārā paṭippassaddhā honti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the second absorption, the placing of the mind and keeping it connected have been tranquilized. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.34"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa pīti paṭippassaddhā hoti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the third absorption, rapture has been tranquilized. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.35"
msgid "Catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa assāsapassāsā paṭippassaddhā honti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the fourth absorption, breathing has been tranquilized. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.36"
msgid "Saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpannassa saññā ca vedanā ca paṭippassaddhā honti. "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling, perception and feeling have been tranquilized. "

msgctxt "sn36.11:2.37"
msgid "Khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno rāgo paṭippassaddho hoti, doso paṭippassaddho hoti, moho paṭippassaddho hotī”ti. "
msgstr "For a mendicant who has ended the defilements, greed, hate, and delusion have been tranquilized.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.11:2.38"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

